FBIS4-38091 "drnes124_p_94013" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Missiles Kill 13 in Kabul LD2806102694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 28 Jun 94 LD2806102694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] In line with the continuation of fighting among the involved sides in the capital of Afghanistan, Kabul city center was this morning subjected to strikes by dozens of missiles. According to a report by the Central News Desk from Kabul, the missiles landed on central parts of Kabul city and caused considerable damage, leaving at least 13 people dead and a large number wounded. The hospital sources in Kabul likewise announced that in the course of the past three days' fighting in Kabul 100 people were killed and 500 were injured. A report by AFP states that a spokesman for the UN secretary general has announced: Within the framework of revival of the political presence of this organization in Afghanistan, a special team will visit this country. He added: Until the security situation improves in Kabul, the UN mission will be established temporarily in Jalalabad.
